summary: Defendant made initial contact with plaintiff via email
Contract agreement signed by both parties
First payment received by plaintiff from defendant
Defendant failed to deliver goods as specified in contract
Plaintiff sent notice of breach to defendant via certified mail
Defendant refused to cure breach after 30-day notice period
Plaintiff engaged legal counsel to pursue remedies
Defendant made partial payment attempt of $10,000
Plaintiff rejected partial payment as insufficient
Defendant ceased all communication with plaintiff
Plaintiff incurred additional costs of $15,000 due to delay
Expert witness retained to assess contract damages
Final demand letter sent to defendant before filing suit
